RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 10 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Louisiana Bred NW2 $5000 & NW3 $5000 Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRUSADER EXPRESS stalked leaders from the rail, saved ground around the turn, was pulled out to the seven path at the quarter pole, hooked foe, matched strides down the lane while catching the early leaders, ran all out in a set of four ,driving to the wire and out finished the other rivals for the win COURAGEOUS TIMMY left a step slow, was able to settle in the second tier behind the earlier leaders, from in between rivals in the two path. dropped back a bit and saved ground around the turn, made a bid from the quarter pole hooking rivals from both sides was driven hard and was up for second. BLUSHINSTREETDEVIL sped away from the gates to have the lead, was hooked with another rival almost stride for stride along the backside and through the turn entering the stretch was bumped by his company continued to trade bumps with same rival back and forth, was caught on the outside by another set of rivals , raced aggressively down to the wire but just missed and settled for third CREME DE BALI broke out at the start ,vied for the early led, hooked another competitor all the way down the back side, stayed on with the battle through the turn, at the top of the lane was brought out to meet foe, but was answered back with the same aggressive racing from the rival, traded bumps, matched strides with the same foe, these two were caught on the outside by another pair of rivaling contestants, in a four way battle for the last sixteenth of a mile, was pushed and driven all the way down to the wire but to no avail. SEMI CHARMED LIFE followed the leaders from between horses in the four path down the backside, saved ground through the turn, rallied from the quarter pole but didn't have enough to to catch leaders and settled for fifth. SIXTO jumped out and settled into the second tier from the outside, stayed with rivals until the turn, dropped back to save ground, was asked at the quarter pole but didn't fire.
